<br>
Still, since the points system is meant to the equitable (points awarded for the raid are meant to equate to the points value of the drops/ price paid by the benefitiary) and therefore the net value of the points pool should be 0 at any one time, we have scope to award RLs more to work off the margin our initial negative balances create.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukilmir123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kilmir123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/23/02 2:56:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fscarab5467frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid leaders points.  </span><hr size=1> Hmm, here is a wild idea. How about the points you get are decided after a raid and when point-costs for loot are all paid.<br>
<br>
After the raid you add all the costs together, then devide the total by the number of participants and give everyone that result. Any non devided points go to the raidleader + 1 (to make sure RL always has some extra).<br>
<br>
This way you on average get more point awards for RL's for larger groups (bigger share left usually because the devision number is so large) and the total amount of earned points is equal to the total amount of used points.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just a wild thought with probably some holes (total amount of points on the whole will only go down with no initial buffer due to players who leave scarab?) but worth looking into? <p>Arch Mage Rhand Kinslayer<br>
